pes are all present. DatabaseMetaData and getMetaData appear in the source as example use cases but aren't included in the hints, though these feel like minor omissions rather than critical gaps.\n\nFor the third section, I'm checking BasicSqlLoader, SchemaReplacer, BasicStatementFactory, and the schema-related properties—all of these match up with the hints. The fourth section looks complete as well, with ConnectionFactorySupport, DefaultDialect, and the exception factory classes all accounted for. The `no_knowledge_content` flag is set to false, so I can skip that validation. Overall, there's just one minor gap in the first section regarding the SQLを使ったデータ note. I'm checking the implementation section more carefully now. The source shows that SQL database access remains unchanged regardless of whether caching is enabled—this is an important detail for developers to know they don't need to modify their code. Combined with the DatabaseMetaData example in s2, these are both minor omissions that don't affect the overall accuracy of the knowledge file. I'm not finding any critical issues here. SQLを使ったデータベースアクセスはキャッシュの有無に関わらず実装が変わらないという点が重要で、開発者はコード変更を気にする必要がないということだね。それから、DatabaseMetaDataの使用例も確認しておく必要があるけど、これは軽微な漏れだ。","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":19813,"cache_read_input_tokens":18400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":19813,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"95139d12-24dc-4cf9-999e-b294c1eb0463","uuid":"9bc56105-b49c-4309-b729-cab686743246"}
